<div id="review_1900518579" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1900518579" />
    <a title="Simona B" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5312173-simona-b"><img alt="Simona B" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1408893128p2/5312173.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1900518579?book_show_action=true">Feb 02, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Simona B" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Simona B" href="/user/show/5312173-simona-b">Simona B</a>
      </span>

          marked it as wishlist




        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1900518579" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12092473662140842907">It seems it will be called <i>The Islands of the Fox</i> and Cornelia said she will be working on it in 2017! Does this mean we can hope for it to be released later this year? OH MY GOD I SO VERY CAN&apos;T.<br/><br/>For info on Cornelia&apos;s plans for 2017: <a target='_blank' rel='noopener nofollow' href='http://www.corneliafunke.com/en/news/mirrorworld-inkworld-and'>http://www.corneliafunke.com/en/news/...</a></span>
  <span id="freeText12092473662140842907" style="display:none">It seems it will be called <i>The Islands of the Fox</i> and Cornelia said she will be working on it in 2017! Does this mean we can hope for it to be released later this year? OH MY GOD I SO VERY CAN'T.<br /><br />For info on Cornelia's plans for 2017: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://www.corneliafunke.com/en/news/mirrorworld-inkworld-and">http://www.corneliafunke.com/en/news/...</a></span>
  <a data-text-id="12092473662140842907" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
