<div id="review_2514388226" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2514388226" />
    <a title="Clare" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/24835874-clare"><img alt="Clare" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1561115477p2/24835874.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2514388226?book_show_action=true">Feb 10, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Clare" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Clare" href="/user/show/24835874-clare">Clare</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2514388226" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11907443661592839190">This only seems to be out in German for now, but I&apos;m sure there&apos;ll be an English translation soon. <br/><br/>The story picks up where book 3 left off, with all the ramifications of the death of the fae and Will running off with two of Jacob&apos;s enemies. I loved how we got to explore Japan this time, or the &apos;Land of the Foxes.&apos; Funke did her research into Shinto religion, and it really shows. Also we&apos;re introduced to a new character, Hideo, who&apos;s covered in tattoos of Japanese mythical animals (the magic he </span>
  <span id="freeText11907443661592839190" style="display:none">This only seems to be out in German for now, but I'm sure there'll be an English translation soon. <br /><br />The story picks up where book 3 left off, with all the ramifications of the death of the fae and Will running off with two of Jacob's enemies. I loved how we got to explore Japan this time, or the 'Land of the Foxes.' Funke did her research into Shinto religion, and it really shows. Also we're introduced to a new character, Hideo, who's covered in tattoos of Japanese mythical animals (the magic he can perform with these is awesome.) <br /><br />I especially loved the scenes with Jacob and his longtime rival Nerron (the Bastard). Seeing their mutual hatred of each other as they were forced to work together made me laugh. We also get to see some more of Orlando, the Albion spy, and Fox gets put in the spotlight more than in the past.<br /><br />I must admit, the story was a bit slow in the middle, particularly when the characters have to split up. Poor Jacob spent most of it unable to do much, which I found pretty frustrating to read. But by the end I could see how Funke set everything up for a much bigger conflict, with Jacob and Fox at its centre. I really can't wait to see how it all goes down in the next book! <br /><br />All in all, although Jacob's lack of agency was frustrating at times, the other characters' arcs, Funke's rich worldbuilding, and multi-faceted villains kept me reading! Also, all those big reveals...<br /> <br />Bring on the next book! (Maybe in 2-3 years? I hope it comes sooner...)</span>
  <a data-text-id="11907443661592839190" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


