<div id="review_3895606371" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3895606371" />
    <a title="Numa Parrott" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2288155-numa-parrott"><img alt="Numa Parrott" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1499368670p2/2288155.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3895606371?book_show_action=true">May 24, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Numa Parrott" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Numa Parrott" href="/user/show/2288155-numa-parrott">Numa Parrott</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Audiobook 9783981653960" href="/book/show/53402459-auf-silberner-f-hrte">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3895606371" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13830766487368240194">I like this Mirrorworld book more than the last two combined. The last two had several scenes I loved, but overall they left me feeling underwhelmed. This book did have a few weaker moments but I haven&apos;t enjoyed a story (that wasn&apos;t Discworld or Dresden Files) this much in a long time. That said--I can&apos;t defend my opinion at all. When I think about what actually happened in this book... the structure of the action, the character motivations, everything that actually happens... it&apos;s very odd. It&apos;</span>
  <span id="freeText13830766487368240194" style="display:none">I like this Mirrorworld book more than the last two combined. The last two had several scenes I loved, but overall they left me feeling underwhelmed. This book did have a few weaker moments but I haven't enjoyed a story (that wasn't Discworld or Dresden Files) this much in a long time. That said--I can't defend my opinion at all. When I think about what actually happened in this book... the structure of the action, the character motivations, everything that actually happens... it's very odd. It's mostly that sweet sweet <b> drama </b> that keeps it flowing. Anyway, my favorite element of these books isn't the characters or the world building, it's the horror. Sure Fox is cool and Jacob is fun to torment and that sumo guy must be protected at all costs and whatever saucy drama is going on between Nerron and Will--yowza--but what gets me are the child-eating witches and the dark elves with death castles. Fantastic. 👏 <br /><br />I half expected this to be the last book for some reason but it's absolutely not.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13830766487368240194" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


